## Creating Issues

Use Jira MCP tools to create issues:
- `jira_create_issue` - Create new issues
- `jira_search_issues` - Search with JQL
- `jira_get_issue` - Get issue details
- `jira_update_issue` - Update existing issues
- `jira_add_comment` - Add comments
- `jira_transition_issue` - Change status

### Example: Create a Bug
```
Create a Jira bug in DT project:
- Title: "Login fails with special characters in password"
- Description: "Users cannot log in when password contains & or < characters"
- Priority: High
```

### Example: Search Issues
```
Search for open bugs: project = DT AND type = Bug AND status != Done
Search my tasks: project = DT AND assignee = currentUser()
```

